WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:03.247
Previously on "Stumptown"...

00:03.250 --> 00:04.706
Sometimes people
have problems.

00:04.710 --> 00:05.995
The kind of problems that
the police can't help with.

00:06.000 --> 00:07.410
Grey: You, a PI?

00:07.420 --> 00:09.160
You can barely find your keys
half the time.

00:09.170 --> 00:10.068
Might keep me
out of trouble.

00:10.080 --> 00:11.661
Hoffman:
She's good. She's smart.

00:11.670 --> 00:14.537
Just don't want you compromising
your professional integrity

00:14.540 --> 00:17.998
for whatever personal dynamic
the two of you might have.

00:18.000 --> 00:20.412
If you want to do this thing
for real,

00:20.420 --> 00:22.661
put in the hours.
Get yourself a license.

00:22.670 --> 00:24.820
Jack Feeney.
Alright!

00:24.830 --> 00:26.616
We're both on the hook
for this money.

00:26.620 --> 00:28.668
We're talking about half a mil.
We got to get on the road.

00:28.670 --> 00:30.786
Everything I got is right here.
I'm not going anywhere.

00:30.790 --> 00:32.781
[ Sirens wailing ]

00:34.540 --> 00:36.417
[ Keyboard clacking ]

00:38.750 --> 00:40.411
[ Clears throat ]

00:40.420 --> 00:41.284
[ Clacking stops ]

00:44.790 --> 00:47.076
[ Clacking resumes ]
Assistant: Mr. Banks
IS on hIS way up.

00:48.250 --> 00:50.536
[ Sirens wailing ]

00:50.540 --> 00:52.747
[ Funk music plays ]

00:52.750 --> 00:55.571
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

01:04.000 --> 01:05.490
[ Engine rewing, tires squeal ]

01:12.920 --> 01:14.569
[ Grunts ]

01:14.580 --> 01:16.536
[ Groans ]

01:16.540 --> 01:18.781
Good thing it's trash day.

01:18.790 --> 01:21.247
[ Whip cracks ]

01:21.250 --> 01:23.036
[ Gunshot ]
This is a robbery!

01:23.040 --> 01:25.702
Come on! You!
Wallet! Now!

01:25.710 --> 01:28.247
Gents...why all the fuss?

01:30.250 --> 01:31.239
[ Glass shatters ]

01:31.250 --> 01:33.957
[ Grunting ]

01:33.960 --> 01:35.530
[ Gun cocks ]

01:35.540 --> 01:37.576
Which one of you clowns
is gonna buy me a drink?

01:37.580 --> 01:39.457
[ Gunshot ]

01:40.580 --> 01:42.662
[ Explosion ]

01:42.670 --> 01:44.490
[ Music slows down, stops ]

01:47.000 --> 01:48.911
[ Clacking continues ]

01:50.460 --> 01:53.577
Assistant: Dex "Pa-rye-ose"
is here for you, sir.

01:53.580 --> 01:54.877
Uh, Mr. Banks?
Beat it.

01:54.880 --> 01:57.030
Excuse me, Mr. Banks?
I just need to have one word --

01:57.040 --> 01:58.109
Wow!

02:02.880 --> 02:04.950
Wait just a minute,
young lady!

02:04.960 --> 02:06.700
You can't go in there!

02:06.710 --> 02:08.701
[ Sighs ]

02:08.710 --> 02:11.702
Pretty crappy business model,
making potential clients wait.

02:11.710 --> 02:13.075
You're not
a potential client.

02:13.080 --> 02:14.911
You're Dexadrine Parios,
33,

02:14.920 --> 02:17.662
former combat Marine
on disability.

02:17.670 --> 02:19.820
Ruder than a mule with a mouth
full of bumblebees --

02:19.830 --> 02:21.377
I coined that back in '83 --

02:21.380 --> 02:24.031
and your checking account's been
overdrawn 16 times this year,

02:24.040 --> 02:25.325
as recently as...

02:25.330 --> 02:26.911
[ Keyboard clacks ]
...last week.

02:26.920 --> 02:28.785
None of your business,
but my brother needed that money

02:28.790 --> 02:29.700
for a soccer tournament.

02:29.710 --> 02:31.496
Sweet story.

02:31.500 --> 02:33.661
But you're still not a potential
client 'cause you're broke.

02:33.670 --> 02:35.069
What kind of name is Dexadrine,
anyway?

02:35.080 --> 02:36.411
Don't call me that.

02:36.420 --> 02:37.910
How much must parents
detest a child

02:37.920 --> 02:38.955
to name them Dexadrine?

02:38.960 --> 02:40.200
I mean, seriously,
you were born,

02:40.210 --> 02:41.609
and they took a look
at you and said,

02:41.620 --> 02:43.110
"Oh, my God. Dexadrine.

02:43.120 --> 02:46.248
Our child reminds us
of generic cough syrup."

02:46.250 --> 02:50.664
Artie isn't exactly on
the Mt. Rushmore of names.

02:50.670 --> 02:52.740
Look, I'm here
because I'm a P.I.

02:52.750 --> 02:55.036
Never heard of you.
I'm currently unlicensed.

02:55.040 --> 02:57.326
I need to get my 1,500 hours
of apprenticeship

02:57.330 --> 02:58.536
so I can be certified
here in Oregon.

02:58.540 --> 03:01.247
There are 522 P.I.'s in Portland
not named --

03:01.250 --> 03:04.492
Arthur Banks.
58 years old.

03:04.500 --> 03:08.072
Youngest minted detective
in Portland PD history.

03:08.080 --> 03:10.412
Served 16 years
before sudden retirement.

03:10.420 --> 03:12.206
Been a P.I. ever since.

03:12.210 --> 03:15.077
Your first major case
was the widow of an Army vet.

03:15.080 --> 03:16.490
You proved
that he was killed

03:16.500 --> 03:20.243
because of substandard care
at a VA hospital.

03:20.250 --> 03:23.708
You fight for the underdog.
I respect that.

03:23.710 --> 03:25.416
What the hell is that?

03:25.420 --> 03:28.116
I'm not sure exactly.
I just know it's expensive.

03:28.120 --> 03:30.577
It's hideous.
It cost $14,000.

03:30.580 --> 03:33.071
[ Chuckles ]

03:33.080 --> 03:35.162
Oh.

03:35.170 --> 03:38.571
Huh. Okay, uh, look,
I have done my research.

03:38.580 --> 03:39.877
You are the best.

03:39.880 --> 03:42.201
If I apprentice under you,
I'm gonna get more clients.

03:42.210 --> 03:43.700
I can increase my rates.

03:43.710 --> 03:45.371
Sell me.

03:45.380 --> 03:47.610
Why should I take time
out of my glorious life

03:47.620 --> 03:49.372
to help you better yours,
Dexadrine?

03:49.380 --> 03:50.995
Dex.

03:51.000 --> 03:53.241
Uh...I need the money.

03:53.250 --> 03:54.490
Nope.

03:54.500 --> 03:56.286
I haven't been doing this
for a very long time,

03:56.290 --> 03:57.075
but I actually think
that I could --

03:57.080 --> 03:59.878
No.

03:59.880 --> 04:01.108
Lemme get my hours,
I'll give you a cut

04:01.120 --> 04:03.202
of all my jobs for a year.

04:03.210 --> 04:04.575
I'll grab my pants,
and let's go.

04:06.170 --> 04:08.286
Hey, Feeney. It's Grey.

04:08.290 --> 04:09.609
Yeah,
I'm just checking in, man.

04:09.620 --> 04:12.327
I_...I want to see
If you left town

04:12.330 --> 04:14.491
and if our friend reached out
to you again, okay?

04:14.500 --> 04:16.161
Hit me back.

04:16.170 --> 04:17.785
[ Cellphone beeps ]

04:17.790 --> 04:19.746
Hey, Feeney. It's Grey.

04:19.750 --> 04:21.456
Yeah,
I'm just checking in, man.

04:21.460 --> 04:23.701
I_...I want to see
If you left town

04:23.710 --> 04:25.780
and if our friend reached out
to you again, okay?

04:25.790 --> 04:27.417
Cosgrove: I just got off
the phone with the mayor.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

04:27.420 --> 04:29.160
Colonoscopy-level joy.

04:29.170 --> 04:30.785
What did he want?
Nothing much.

04:30.790 --> 04:33.247
Body gets dumped under a bridge,
two bullet holes to the back.

04:33.250 --> 04:34.376
My guess --
he wants to know

04:34.380 --> 04:35.495
what the hell
we're doing about it.

04:35.500 --> 04:36.615
I'm on it.
I have a lead.

04:36.620 --> 04:38.417
Bar owner.
Grey McConnell.

04:38.420 --> 04:41.412
Okay.
Last person to leave a message
on the vic's phone.

04:41.420 --> 04:42.990
He's also a friend
of Dex Parios.

04:45.500 --> 04:50.039
Have you ever...been to Tokyo,
Hoffman?

04:50.040 --> 04:52.747
No.
So, there's this dog.

04:52.750 --> 04:55.787
I don't remember his name,
but he would meet his owner

04:55.790 --> 04:57.781
at the train station
every day after work.

04:57.790 --> 04:59.781
Anyway, the guy passes away
on the job,

04:59.790 --> 05:03.374
but the dog continues to show up
every single day,

05:03.380 --> 05:05.280
hoping to see his owner.

05:05.290 --> 05:09.283
Eight years.
Until the dog died.

05:09.290 --> 05:11.451
I get it, Lieutenant.

05:11.460 --> 05:12.916
_Feels like Dex
IS everywhere.

05:12.920 --> 05:14.569
Dex isn't the dog.

05:19.460 --> 05:21.872
Candace is in the middle
of a nasty divorce battle

05:21.880 --> 05:24.371
with Randall Tapper, mega-rich
real-estate developer.

05:24.380 --> 05:26.325
He's got more people
in his pocket than I do.

05:26.330 --> 05:28.457
He's constantly dropping loot
on charities,

05:28.460 --> 05:31.247
opening kids' hospitals,
boring stuff like that

05:31.250 --> 05:33.741
so he can continue to appear
like the Archangel Gabriel.

05:33.750 --> 05:36.287
But_it works.
He's got this town greased.

05:36.290 --> 05:39.828
We're here to convince Candace
that we can flip the script.

05:39.830 --> 05:43.118
What am I supposed to do?
Don't talk. Until it's time
to talk. Then talk.

05:43.120 --> 05:44.610
How will I --
You'll know.

05:45.750 --> 05:48.787
[ Knock on door ]

05:48.790 --> 05:50.781
Artie Banks,
elite private investigator.

05:50.790 --> 05:52.496
[ Baby coos ]
We spoke on the phone.

05:54.170 --> 05:56.286
My final custody hearing
is next week,

05:56.290 --> 05:58.167
and the deck is completely
stacked against me.

05:58.170 --> 05:59.410
[ Baby coos ]

05:59.420 --> 06:01.160
Why do you guys
want to help me?

06:01.170 --> 06:03.161
I get 10% of the divorce
settlement.

06:03.170 --> 06:05.912
[ Sighs ]
Capped at $200,000.

06:05.920 --> 06:08.320
Look, I've been burned
a lot this year...

06:08.330 --> 06:10.457
by people saying
they want to help me,

06:10.460 --> 06:12.951
only to back out because
of Randall's influence.

06:12.960 --> 06:13.995
I don't know what
you're going through,

06:14.000 --> 06:15.570
but I can tell you this --

06:15.580 --> 06:17.821
we can help.

06:21.750 --> 06:23.615
Yeah, um...

06:23.620 --> 06:25.372
I take care
of my brother.

06:25.380 --> 06:26.870
It's just him and me.

06:26.880 --> 06:29.326
My parents, they...well,
it doesn't matter,

06:29.330 --> 06:32.663
but, um, you know,
he's all I got.

06:32.670 --> 06:34.877
I can't imagine anyone ever
coming and taking him away.

06:34.880 --> 06:39.169
I...I-I-I wouldn't
let them.

06:39.170 --> 06:40.614
So...

06:44.670 --> 06:47.616
Okay.
Let's do this.

06:47.620 --> 06:48.700
I can't give up.

06:48.710 --> 06:50.200
If you were to dig up
dirt on Randall,

06:50.210 --> 06:51.700
where would you start?

06:51.710 --> 06:53.246
His business.

06:53.250 --> 06:55.206
Randall will do anything
to make a buck.

06:58.460 --> 07:01.918
I want a fresh start,
for me and my daughter.

07:01.920 --> 07:04.036
[ Sirens wailing,
dog barking ]

07:04.040 --> 07:05.246
Here you go.

07:05.250 --> 07:08.287
What's this?
Finder's fee.

07:08.290 --> 07:09.700
You _used me
to manipulate her,

07:09.710 --> 07:11.826
and now you're gonna give me
a couple of bills

07:11.830 --> 07:13.377
when you could be collecting
200K?

07:13.380 --> 07:14.699
Exactly right.

07:14.710 --> 07:16.701
First rule of private
investigation --

07:16.710 --> 07:18.575
manipulation
is your best weapon.

07:18.580 --> 07:21.322
Listen, I'm not really good
at this mentoring thing,

07:21.330 --> 07:23.457
so this is your first
and last lesson.

07:23.460 --> 07:27.908
So, take it in, cherish it,
breathe deep,

07:27.920 --> 07:29.410
and learn to live with it.

07:29.420 --> 07:31.911
Okay, you know,
I-I think your client --

07:31.920 --> 07:34.377
she's gonna be pretty upset
when I just disappear.

07:34.380 --> 07:35.779
You still have this case
because of me,

07:35.790 --> 07:37.109
so here's what's
gonna happen, okay?

07:37.120 --> 07:39.202
I'm staying, you're gonna sign
my apprentice hours

07:39.210 --> 07:40.825
when we're done,
and you're gonna give me 2%

07:40.830 --> 07:42.320
of whatever you collect
from Candace.

07:46.330 --> 07:49.413
Are you in it for the cash
or for the girl?

07:49.420 --> 07:52.207
20% girl, 80% cash.

07:52.210 --> 07:53.529
There's hope for you yet.

07:53.540 --> 07:54.916
So, now what?

07:54.920 --> 07:56.490
We bug Tapper's office.

07:56.500 --> 07:58.070
Is that even legal?

07:58.080 --> 07:59.991
For me, highly illegal
because I'm licensed.

08:00.000 --> 08:02.321
For you,
it's only vaguely unethical.

08:02.330 --> 08:04.161
Well, how am I supposed to get
into Tapper's office?

08:04.170 --> 08:05.614
We go shopping.

08:15.380 --> 08:17.029
Raji: No, you're killing me
here, man.

08:17.040 --> 08:19.668
We had a deal. We had --
Yeah, no.

08:19.670 --> 08:21.535
I'm saying what we need
to get done is this right now.

08:21.540 --> 08:23.952
Uh, deliveries
for Mr. Tapper.

08:23.960 --> 08:25.530
Thandie sick again?
Yeah, I'm filling in.

08:25.540 --> 08:26.700
Yeah -- No, no, no.

08:26.710 --> 08:28.371
Mr. Tapper doesn't want
a Chagall.

08:28.380 --> 08:31.326
He wants a Mir.
Eh -- Hold on.

08:31.330 --> 08:33.742
Uh, letters in the bin on
the desk, packages in the box.

08:33.750 --> 08:35.786
Got it.
How -- How far
do we go back, man?

08:35.790 --> 08:37.200
I was in your bar mitzvah!

08:37.210 --> 08:38.916
Yeah, for sure.
Oh, okay.

08:44.040 --> 08:45.917
[ Sighs ]

08:48.920 --> 08:50.785
What?

08:53.710 --> 08:54.995
Good afternoon, Mr. Tapper.

08:55.000 --> 08:55.739
What do you got for me?

08:55.750 --> 08:58.071
Your afternoon schedule.

08:58.080 --> 09:00.708
Oh, uh, your 4:00 PM.
was pushed, and...

09:00.710 --> 09:03.110
unfortunately,
the Mir is no longer for sale.

09:03.120 --> 09:04.747
Everything is for sale,
Raji.

09:08.290 --> 09:10.372
Well, you're new.
Oh, hello.

09:10.380 --> 09:12.450
Randall Tapper.
Oh. Dex.

09:12.460 --> 09:14.416
Well,
glad to have you, Dex.

09:14.420 --> 09:16.411
Eh, tag is still
on your jacket.

09:16.420 --> 09:17.990
Oh.
Eh, it's fine.

09:18.000 --> 09:20.457
It's -- Sorry.
it's really bothering me.

09:20.460 --> 09:21.870
You don't -- Oh.
Yeah.

09:21.880 --> 09:23.666
See? Not a problem.
Got it.

09:23.670 --> 09:25.069
And welcome.

09:25.080 --> 09:26.957
My door's open
if you ever have any problem.

09:26.960 --> 09:29.372
Genuinely.
Thank you.

09:33.880 --> 09:35.780
Oh, I need a beer.

09:35.790 --> 09:37.451
[ Grunts ]
And new feet.

09:37.460 --> 09:40.247
The wire's up and running.
Oh, good.

09:40.250 --> 09:41.615
I hope you didn't
mess up that suit.

09:41.620 --> 09:42.780
I want to return it.

09:45.830 --> 09:47.661
You got talent.

09:47.670 --> 09:50.377
You're green,
but you could be good, Dex.

09:52.960 --> 09:54.370
[ Car rumbling ]

09:56.750 --> 09:58.240
Hey.
What the --

09:58.250 --> 09:59.285
[ Metal clanks ]

09:59.290 --> 10:00.370
Oh!

10:00.380 --> 10:02.280
[Tires squeal ]

10:02.290 --> 10:03.496
Hey, is that our --
Yep.

10:03.500 --> 10:05.707
[Tires squeal ]

10:05.710 --> 10:07.325
[ Car horn blares ]

10:07.330 --> 10:09.958
[Tires squealing,
car horns honking ]

10:09.960 --> 10:11.109
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no.

10:11.120 --> 10:11.996
Brake it! Brake it!
Brake it! Brake it!

10:12.000 --> 10:13.410
[ Screams ]
Brake it! Oh, no!

10:23.210 --> 10:24.871
Wheels don't
just fall off of cars.

10:24.880 --> 10:26.416
That was sabotage.
Dex: So, what?

10:26.420 --> 10:27.569
They're --
They're trying to kill us?

10:27.580 --> 10:28.911
Or warn us off.

10:28.920 --> 10:31.491
It was either Randall
or some Portland scum activist

10:31.500 --> 10:33.240
mad salty I drive an SUV.

10:33.250 --> 10:35.036
Neither of those
are comforting.

10:35.040 --> 10:38.532
Dex, as a veteran P.I.,
I consider myself a leprechaun,

10:38.540 --> 10:40.667
and danger is the rainbow
leading to the pot of gold.

10:40.670 --> 10:43.116
Yeah, I got it.

10:43.120 --> 10:44.280
Yep.

10:46.460 --> 10:49.247
_ _You know
this isn't a real car?

10:49.250 --> 10:51.491
It's a golf cart
with doors.

10:51.500 --> 10:52.910
Well, it works.

10:52.920 --> 10:54.911
It's_ not totaled
like yours.

10:54.920 --> 10:56.569
[ Car hits bump,
tape deck whirs ]

10:56.580 --> 10:58.992
I can sense your needs

10:59.000 --> 11:01.321
Like rain unto the seeds
It's...

11:01.330 --> 11:03.036
It's weird.

11:03.040 --> 11:04.826
...of confusion in your mind

11:04.830 --> 11:06.240
[Volume decreases ]

11:06.250 --> 11:07.490
[ Sighs ]

11:07.500 --> 11:10.378
I know Chaka.
Her uncle was extorting her.

11:10.380 --> 11:11.779
Late '905.

11:11.790 --> 11:14.748
I convinced him
to back off.

11:14.750 --> 11:17.162
Three weeks later,
we were sipping Dom

11:17.170 --> 11:20.958
in a villa in Mykonos.

11:20.960 --> 11:23.372
She's a very...

11:23.380 --> 11:24.870
sensual woman.

11:27.880 --> 11:31.111
I'm every woman

11:31.120 --> 11:33.918
It's all in me

11:33.920 --> 11:36.161
[ Rock music plays ]

11:36.170 --> 11:37.614
Dex ain't here, man.

11:37.620 --> 11:39.997
Not here for Dex.
I'm here for a Manhattan.

11:40.000 --> 11:41.570
Rye or bourbon
in that Manhattan?

11:41.580 --> 11:43.662
Bourbon.
Bourbon.

11:43.670 --> 11:46.070
Must be nice opening a bar
in your hometown.

11:46.080 --> 11:47.206
Oh, I'm not from Portland.

11:47.210 --> 11:50.327
Oh, yeah? Stumptown.
Born and raised.

11:50.330 --> 11:53.072
Me and my buddies --
we always wanted to open a bar.

11:53.080 --> 11:54.957
Hey, rude question,
but I'm curious --

11:54.960 --> 11:57.167
what's it cost to get something
like this off the ground?

11:59.040 --> 12:00.780
Rye.

12:00.790 --> 12:02.872
Better, in my opinion.

12:02.880 --> 12:05.576
You did time with Jack Feeney,
yeah?

12:05.580 --> 12:07.878
Name sounds familiar, but I did
time with a lot of folks.

12:07.880 --> 12:11.372
Just asking. He was floating
around Portland also.

12:11.380 --> 12:12.824
Prison's not a frat.
We don't do reunions.

12:12.830 --> 12:15.116
[ Both laugh ]

12:15.120 --> 12:16.200
Funny.
Yeah.

12:16.210 --> 12:17.825
That's funny.

12:17.830 --> 12:19.821
I don't know. I mean,
you turned things around.

12:19.830 --> 12:21.457
Opened a bar.

12:21.460 --> 12:23.917
I thought maybe
he'd reach out to you.

12:23.920 --> 12:25.376
How's the drink?

12:31.460 --> 12:32.870
[ Clears throat ]
Meant to come by Tuesday night,

12:32.880 --> 12:35.166
but I got held up.

12:35.170 --> 12:36.910
Were you here?
I always am.

12:36.920 --> 12:38.410
Is there anything else
I can help you with?

12:38.420 --> 12:39.990
I'm just making
conversation.

12:40.000 --> 12:41.570
I'm not that type
of bartender.

12:45.460 --> 12:48.202
You know...

12:48.210 --> 12:49.825
not a big fan of rye.

12:49.830 --> 12:52.617
16 bucks.

12:52.620 --> 12:53.826
All yours.

12:56.210 --> 12:58.826
You know, I know you two
don't keep in touch,

12:58.830 --> 13:01.822
but, uh...

13:01.830 --> 13:03.878
Feeney's dead.

13:03.880 --> 13:06.826
Whoever shot him did it
while he was running away.

13:12.420 --> 13:14.615
Hey.
What are you doing here?

13:14.620 --> 13:18.078
Day off. Thought I'd just check
this place out for real.

13:18.080 --> 13:20.207
Artie Banks?
Detective Hoffman.

13:20.210 --> 13:21.325
Do you guys
know each other?

13:21.330 --> 13:23.878
Yeah, Artie's a legend
in these streets.

13:23.880 --> 13:26.667
But no one seems to know why he
left the force back in the day.

13:26.670 --> 13:27.955
I don't know what kind
of car you drive,

13:27.960 --> 13:30.576
but I'm pretty sure
it's not a sick Mustang.

13:30.580 --> 13:32.957
Excuse me.

13:32.960 --> 13:36.202
Yeah, I'm apprenticing
or whatever with Artie.

13:36.210 --> 13:37.165
You know,
locking in my hours.

13:37.170 --> 13:39.240
Making this
P.I. thing official?

13:39.250 --> 13:40.410
Trying to.

13:40.420 --> 13:42.490
Respect.

13:42.500 --> 13:43.706
What is his deal?
He seems a little --

13:43.710 --> 13:44.699
Weird?
Yeah.

13:44.710 --> 13:46.496
Yeah, sure.

13:46.500 --> 13:47.956
But he's great
at what he does.

13:49.920 --> 13:51.569
Look, you're definitely gonna
learn something.

13:51.580 --> 13:52.877
[ Chuckles ]

13:52.880 --> 13:55.371
Just don't go
all big time on me.

13:55.380 --> 13:56.995
No, I won't.

14:00.330 --> 14:02.958
Grey...this is Artie.
Artie, Grey.

14:02.960 --> 14:04.075
Hey.

14:04.080 --> 14:05.661
Dex says we drink here
for free.

14:09.790 --> 14:11.030
[ Groans ]

14:12.960 --> 14:15.667
Hey.
Something wrong with you?

14:15.670 --> 14:17.786
Other than you offering
your sweetheart drink deal

14:17.790 --> 14:19.246
to every P.I. in Portland?

14:19.250 --> 14:20.877
[ Scoffs ]
If you want me to pay, I'll pay.

14:20.880 --> 14:23.701
That's a lie.
It's a huge lie.

14:23.710 --> 14:25.280
[ Chuckles lightly ]
I don't know. You just
seem a little off.

14:25.290 --> 14:27.451
No, I'm good.

14:27.460 --> 14:28.916
Dex.

14:31.290 --> 14:32.450
What's up?

14:32.460 --> 14:34.746
Tapper just called his bank,
made a wire transfer

14:34.750 --> 14:36.786
of $2,000
from his personal account.

14:36.790 --> 14:39.668
So?
That's not Daddy Warbucks
real-estate money.

14:39.670 --> 14:41.615
Plus,
he called it in himself.

14:41.620 --> 14:43.201
I've been at this game
a long time.

14:43.210 --> 14:44.575
My gut tells me whatever's
on the other end

14:44.580 --> 14:47.458
of that _wire transfer
is dirt.

14:47.460 --> 14:49.997
Okay. Well, who did Tapper
wire the money to?

14:50.000 --> 14:51.956
Stephanie Houston.

14:51.960 --> 14:53.325
Stephanie: Look who it is.

14:53.330 --> 14:56.117
America's least favorite white,
cisgendered P.I.

14:56.120 --> 14:58.611
I have no idea what the hell
that is, but I'm sure I hate it.

14:58.620 --> 15:02.329
What's up? This is an incredibly
challenging chain stitch.

15:02.330 --> 15:04.958
Why is Randall Tapper wiring
money to a Portland madam?

15:06.540 --> 15:08.110
You're a madam, he's a John,
we're P.I.'s --

15:08.120 --> 15:11.248
Dude, your patriarchal terms for
sex work are killing my vibe.

15:11.250 --> 15:14.663
I know Randall Tapper sent you
$2,000 today.

15:14.670 --> 15:17.036
In fact, I dug a little deeper,
into your trash bins --

15:17.040 --> 15:18.610
Actually, I did that.

15:18.620 --> 15:21.032
...and my associate
found bank statements confirming

15:21.040 --> 15:24.419
Randall's been sending you
a recurring wire of $2,000.

15:24.420 --> 15:26.160
How many months
has that been going on for?

15:26.170 --> 15:28.411
My business is built
on discretion.

15:28.420 --> 15:30.615
Discretion [chuckles lightly]
is integral

15:30.620 --> 15:32.247
to my business as well.

15:32.250 --> 15:34.787
I have a long payroll
and really powerful clients,

15:34.790 --> 15:36.610
and I know
that with one phone call,

15:36.620 --> 15:38.167
I could sink your business.

15:41.210 --> 15:43.496
So, we just need you to confirm
that Randall Tapper's

15:43.500 --> 15:45.707
utilizing your services,
and then we can all go back

15:45.710 --> 15:49.328
about our respective
businesses...with discretion.

15:52.460 --> 15:55.281
When I began this,
I was just matching

15:55.290 --> 15:57.667
college girls
with rich friends.

15:57.670 --> 16:00.662
Randall isn't paying me
for new women.

16:00.670 --> 16:03.070
It's hush money.

16:03.080 --> 16:08.780
I sent him one girl
a long time ago.

16:08.790 --> 16:11.167
He married her.

16:11.170 --> 16:13.821
Why lie to the only people
who are trying to help you?

16:13.830 --> 16:15.411
What?
I didn't lie to you.

16:15.420 --> 16:17.206
You could've told us you were a
prostitute when you met Randall.

16:17.210 --> 16:18.529
[ Sighs ]
Artie, come on.

16:18.540 --> 16:20.246
That is not true.

16:20.250 --> 16:21.820
Stephanie Houston
says otherwise.

16:21.830 --> 16:23.206
You knocked on my door.

16:23.210 --> 16:24.370
Now you're coming
at me like this?

16:24.380 --> 16:26.780
Alright, let's just back off
a bit, alright?

16:26.790 --> 16:28.610
Can you just tell us
what is going on?

16:28.620 --> 16:30.918
[ Sighs ]

16:30.920 --> 16:33.571
I was a broke
college student from Wyoming.

16:33.580 --> 16:35.957
Naive.
[ Baby crying ]

16:35.960 --> 16:40.533
I wanted to be independent,
but living on your own is real.

16:40.540 --> 16:42.167
I had real bills.

16:42.170 --> 16:44.661
So, I met this woman
at a bar who told me

16:44.670 --> 16:49.039
that she knew people --
men that were willing to help.

16:49.040 --> 16:50.871
I went on a date
with Randall.

16:50.880 --> 16:53.747
48 hours later, I was having
dinner with him in Rome.

16:53.750 --> 16:56.571
It was an arrangement...

16:56.580 --> 16:59.208
until I fell in love with him
like everybody else does.

16:59.210 --> 17:00.746
He can use this
against you.

17:00.750 --> 17:02.160
He won't.

17:02.170 --> 17:03.489
It would be bad for his image,

17:03.500 --> 17:04.990
which would be bad
for his business,

17:05.000 --> 17:06.376
and that's the only thing

17:06.380 --> 17:07.870
he cares about more
than punishing me.

17:10.170 --> 17:11.876
I'm gonna lose my kid.

17:14.000 --> 17:15.956
So, do you want
to judge me some more,

17:15.960 --> 17:17.279
or do what you promised
you'd do?

17:19.250 --> 17:20.456
[ Knock on door ]

17:20.460 --> 17:23.532
[ Inhales deeply,
dog barking in background ]

17:23.540 --> 17:24.666
Huh.

17:24.670 --> 17:26.069
Weird.

17:27.500 --> 17:28.990
Hello.

17:29.000 --> 17:30.877
May I come in?

17:30.880 --> 17:32.780
[ Insects chirping ]

17:34.290 --> 17:39.785
Well...this is
as I'd expect.

17:39.790 --> 17:42.202
No one th_rows shade
qUIte like you.

17:42.210 --> 17:44.246
You want a beer?
I don't drink beer.

17:44.250 --> 17:46.286
Good, 'cause this is
my last one.

17:46.290 --> 17:47.666
I-I don't know
why you're here,

17:47.670 --> 17:49.570
but, uh, I'm on a case
right now,

17:49.580 --> 17:51.662
one with a pretty fat payday
at the end, so...

17:51.670 --> 17:53.877
There's no payday
at the end of this.

17:53.880 --> 17:55.871
Simply pain
and embarrassment.

17:55.880 --> 17:58.110
Randall Tapper is a friend.

17:58.120 --> 18:02.204
He tells me there's a P.I. named
Artie Banks digging in on him.

18:02.210 --> 18:04.030
I'm not sure
what that has to do with me.

18:04.040 --> 18:05.951
Do you think I came down here
on a hunch?

18:05.960 --> 18:08.030
Portland is a small town.

18:08.040 --> 18:10.372
[ Chuckles ]
What are you into with him?

18:10.380 --> 18:13.611
Randall is a supporter
of the Confederated Tribes.

18:13.620 --> 18:16.327
That means I don't enjoy folks
trying to take him down.

18:16.330 --> 18:17.911
Well,
I appreciate you popping in,

18:17.920 --> 18:19.706
but it's getting
kind of late.

18:19.710 --> 18:21.871
Name your price.

18:21.880 --> 18:25.031
Pnce?
For backing off of Randall.

18:25.040 --> 18:27.577
You know, there's a woman --
his wife --

18:27.580 --> 18:30.287
whose life
he is destroying?

18:30.290 --> 18:32.702
I don't get involved
in other people's relationships.

18:32.710 --> 18:35.452
[ Chuckles ]

18:35.460 --> 18:37.075
Oh, wow.

18:37.080 --> 18:39.378
God, this is an odd way
to thank me

18:39.380 --> 18:42.417
for saving your granddaughter
from -- oh, what was it?

18:42.420 --> 18:43.739
Ah.

18:43.750 --> 18:44.910
It was murder.

18:44.920 --> 18:46.706
Randall is off limits.

18:46.710 --> 18:48.996
I say this with a smile.
Next time, I won't be smiling.

18:50.500 --> 18:53.412
That's too bad.

18:53.420 --> 18:55.911
The righteous man
takes his life in his hand

18:55.920 --> 18:58.457
every time
he utters the truth.

18:58.460 --> 18:59.996
Be careful, Dex.

19:04.790 --> 19:06.280
[ Footsteps departing ]

19:09.540 --> 19:11.246
[Telephones ringing ]

19:11.250 --> 19:13.241
What's the latest
on Grey McConnell?

19:13.250 --> 19:14.990
I approached him
for an informal interview,

19:15.000 --> 19:16.570
and he was, uh, evasive.

19:16.580 --> 19:18.787
So, is he a liar
or a suspect?

19:18.790 --> 19:20.246
That's what I'm trying
to figure out.

19:20.250 --> 19:22.992
His alibi is that he was at
his bar the night of the murder.

19:23.000 --> 19:24.661
Oh, what's the bar?
[ Pen clicks ]

19:24.670 --> 19:26.490
The Bad Alibi.

19:26.500 --> 19:28.570
[ Exhales sharply]
That is an unfortunate name.

19:28.580 --> 19:29.706
[ Snorts ]
Mm.

19:29.710 --> 19:31.450
You been able to confirm?

19:31.460 --> 19:34.452
As of yet, no.
You said that he was a friend
of Parios, right?

19:34.460 --> 19:37.111
I don't think it's a good move
to bring Dex in.

19:37.120 --> 19:39.031
She can confirm
or deny his alibi.

19:39.040 --> 19:41.497
Yeah, but she's too smart to
give up anything at the station.

19:41.500 --> 19:43.877
_I do not have another
timely Japanese parable

19:43.880 --> 19:46.451
to share with you right now,
but I hope that you think

19:46.460 --> 19:49.372
you're smarter
than Dex, Detective.

19:49.380 --> 19:50.870
I can always go
and hire her.

19:50.880 --> 19:53.826
Hmm.

19:53.830 --> 19:54.819
Understood, Lieutenant.

19:54.830 --> 19:56.070
Alright.

19:58.330 --> 20:00.116
[Telephone rings ]

20:01.710 --> 20:03.200
I hate this.

20:03.210 --> 20:05.531
Stakeouts are for rookie
investigators.

20:05.540 --> 20:08.668
Well, we had no choice
after your bug went dead.

20:08.670 --> 20:11.321
Tapper keeps
a strict routine.

20:11.330 --> 20:15.118
Gym, work, golf,
dinner, home.

20:15.120 --> 20:17.031
Nothing at all to help Candace,
so...

20:17.040 --> 20:18.826
He still manages
to make the headlines.

20:18.830 --> 20:21.287
Let me see that.

20:21.290 --> 20:23.872
Sue Lynn Blackbird
came to see me last night.

20:23.880 --> 20:25.745
She told me
to back off Tapper.

20:25.750 --> 20:27.240
"Name your price,"
she said.

20:27.250 --> 20:30.287
We're gonna make so much cash
we can wipe our mouths with it.

20:32.710 --> 20:35.873
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

20:35.880 --> 20:37.529
[ Cellphone beeps ]

20:37.540 --> 20:40.202
Hoffman? _
Hoffman: I am inVIting you
to dinner.

20:40.210 --> 20:42.075
Oh. I decline.

20:42.080 --> 20:43.911
Why?
I'm gonna cook.

20:43.920 --> 20:46.411
'Cause that sounds like a date,
and dates are for...

20:46.420 --> 20:47.990
normal people.

20:48.000 --> 20:51.993
Besides, I thought that we were,
you know, a one-night thing?

20:52.000 --> 20:53.456
You do eat,
don't you, Dex?

20:53.460 --> 20:55.246
Alone, in my car.

20:55.250 --> 20:56.877
Plus, I'm at work.

20:56.880 --> 20:58.666
Oh, yeah.
In perpetuity?

21:01.290 --> 21:03.110
Listen, call it whatever
you want to call it.

21:03.120 --> 21:04.701
You're coming over.
[ Chuckles ]

21:04.710 --> 21:06.951
Or I'm gonna bring dinner
to your car.

21:06.960 --> 21:08.575
Either way,
you're eating with me.

21:08.580 --> 21:12.072
Um...

21:12.080 --> 21:13.911
_ So?
[ Sighs ]'Yeah

21:13.920 --> 21:15.205
Okay.

21:15.210 --> 21:16.746
Tomorrow night.
My place.

21:16.750 --> 21:18.536
Great.

21:18.540 --> 21:20.917
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Hoffman's a good cop.

21:20.920 --> 21:22.990
He might know something
about our target.

21:23.000 --> 21:24.786
First rule of private
investigating --

21:24.790 --> 21:26.997
exploit your contacts.
Yeah?

21:27.000 --> 21:29.992
And if this thing with Hoffman
doesn't lead us aanhere?

21:30.000 --> 21:33.538
First rule of life --
people don't change.

21:33.540 --> 21:35.701
If Tapper's taken a shine
to being a sugar daddy,

21:35.710 --> 21:37.075
he hasn't changed.

21:37.080 --> 21:39.116
There's a new Candace
out there.

21:39.120 --> 21:40.917
You want to know what
the second rule of life is?

21:40.920 --> 21:42.740
Not really.
It's the same.

21:42.750 --> 21:44.411
People don't change.

21:44.420 --> 21:46.115
They might switch things up
a bit,

21:46.120 --> 21:48.202
but they always go back
to who they are.

21:48.210 --> 21:50.166
Well, that's it.
What?

21:50.170 --> 21:52.070
Tapper is not gonna lead us
anywhere, not now.

21:52.080 --> 21:53.741
I mean,
if he's doing dirt,

21:53.750 --> 21:56.321
he's gonna be extra careful
about it.

21:56.330 --> 21:58.036
We're following
the wrong guy.

21:58.830 --> 22:00.491
Tapper's manservant Raji

22:00.500 --> 22:02.115
is definitely doing
his dirty work for him.

22:02.120 --> 22:04.668
About time we got crunk.

22:04.670 --> 22:05.785
Crunk?

22:05.790 --> 22:07.917
[ Funk music plays ]

22:07.920 --> 22:09.820
Basic GPS tracker.

22:09.830 --> 22:10.569
Turn it on like so --

22:10.580 --> 22:12.070
Mm-hmm.

22:12.080 --> 22:14.036
...attaches to the undercarriage
of the vehicle.

22:14.040 --> 22:15.917
Wherever Raji goes,
we follow.

22:15.920 --> 22:17.160
You want me to do this?

22:17.170 --> 22:18.285
Or have your apprentice
do it.

22:34.920 --> 22:36.569
[ Car alarm chirps ]

22:44.040 --> 22:47.328
[ Sighs ]

22:47.330 --> 22:49.412
[ Car alarm chirps ]

22:49.420 --> 22:50.739
Of course.
Why do I need anything else?

22:56.080 --> 22:57.661
[ Engine starts ]

23:13.500 --> 23:14.489
[ Sighs ]

23:17.790 --> 23:19.826
[Jazz music plays ]
[ Knock on door ]

23:29.670 --> 23:33.413
[ Sniffs ] Mmm.
Smells like, uh...food.

23:33.420 --> 23:37.618
Salmon, roasted asparagus,
cheddar mashed potatoes.

23:37.620 --> 23:39.076
Wow.

23:39.080 --> 23:40.957
Mom's recipe.
Beer?

23:40.960 --> 23:43.781
Yeah, thanks.
Cheers.

23:43.790 --> 23:45.746
And jazz.

23:45.750 --> 23:47.160
It's a...|ittle clich,
no?

23:47.170 --> 23:49.491
Not just jazz.
It's Mingus.

23:49.500 --> 23:52.378
Okay, not everybody
can handle Mingus.

23:52.380 --> 23:54.325
Hmm.
Get this fish
out of the oven.

23:58.000 --> 24:00.821
What's all this?

24:00.830 --> 24:02.991
Murder investigation.

24:03.000 --> 24:06.163
Jack Feeney.
You know him?

24:06.170 --> 24:08.206
Why would I know him?

24:08.210 --> 24:10.917
He's just been around Portland.
Just asking.

24:14.620 --> 24:16.451
Yeah, no, I've been,
uh, [exhales sharply]

24:16.460 --> 24:18.951
been tied up with Artie
on this case.

24:18.960 --> 24:20.075
Uh, Randall Tapper.

24:20.080 --> 24:21.377
Real-estate developer?

24:21.380 --> 24:24.031
Yeah, you know him?
He's a friend of the PD.

24:24.040 --> 24:25.450
Two years ago,
he outfitted

24:25.460 --> 24:27.576
the entire department
with new body armor.

24:27.580 --> 24:28.990
Alright.

24:33.380 --> 24:35.666
Nice bar.

24:35.670 --> 24:38.662
Which bar?
Your buddy's place.
McConnell?

24:41.170 --> 24:43.536
Is he there every night?

24:43.540 --> 24:45.531
Well, you should have
asked him yourself.

24:45.540 --> 24:47.576
You like _
your salmon medium?

24:47.580 --> 24:48.820
Sure.

24:48.830 --> 24:50.161
[ Plates scrape ]

24:54.710 --> 24:56.996
Yeah, so I think Tapper
has a taste for prostitutes.

24:59.620 --> 25:02.669
Wish that were a unique trait
for rich, white dudes.

25:02.670 --> 25:05.787
[ Chuckles ]

25:05.790 --> 25:07.166
Does Grey live at the bar?

25:07.170 --> 25:08.990
You should have invited
Grey to dinner.

25:09.000 --> 25:10.536
Just making small talk.

25:10.540 --> 25:12.531
No, you're not...
making small talk.

25:12.540 --> 25:14.246
You're _--
You're working me.

25:14.250 --> 25:17.287
You know that I was military
intelligence, right?

25:17.290 --> 25:18.416
Do you think that Grey
had something to do

25:18.420 --> 25:19.535
with this guy's murder?

25:19.540 --> 25:20.575
I didn't say that.

25:22.460 --> 25:23.779
Well.

25:23.790 --> 25:25.109
This was great.

25:27.330 --> 25:29.616
Dex. Okay.
[ Clears throat ]

25:29.620 --> 25:32.327
Am I really the only one
that's working here?

25:32.330 --> 25:35.663
Huh? I'm pretty sure you're
playing me for intel on Tapper.

25:35.670 --> 25:37.490
Okay.
You're leaving?

25:37.500 --> 25:39.115
Yeah, apparently I am,
because neither of us

25:39.120 --> 25:40.075
are gonna get
what we want, so...

25:40.080 --> 25:42.412
If you think I invited
you over here

25:42.420 --> 25:44.456
just to interrogate you,
you don't know me at all.

25:44.460 --> 25:46.826
I don't know you at all.

25:46.830 --> 25:49.037
I'd like that to change.

25:52.120 --> 25:57.706
if you only came
to get intel on Tapper.

25:57.710 --> 25:59.780
You're here.

25:59.790 --> 26:01.530
I like that.

26:01.540 --> 26:03.110
[ Sighs ]

26:03.120 --> 26:06.032
I don't want you to go.

26:06.040 --> 26:08.873
You know, Grey had nothing to do
with whatever...

26:08.880 --> 26:11.371
happenedtothatguy,
okay?

26:11.380 --> 26:14.372
Yeah,
I'm done talking about Grey.

26:18.620 --> 26:21.578
Are you trying
to seduce me?

26:21.580 --> 26:22.490
[ Smooches ]

26:22.500 --> 26:25.788
Is that what I'm doing?

26:25.790 --> 26:26.950
It's not working.

26:29.500 --> 26:31.411
Feels like it is.

26:31.420 --> 26:34.162
Really?
[ Smooches ]

26:34.170 --> 26:35.410
Really.

26:37.960 --> 26:39.951
Listen, if we do this,

26:39.960 --> 26:42.110
it's not because
you seduced me, okay?

26:42.120 --> 26:43.667
It's because
I want to get off.

26:58.330 --> 26:59.536
Oof.

26:59.540 --> 27:01.167
If you want, I could heat up
the food for you.

27:01.170 --> 27:02.614
Nah, I'm good.

27:02.620 --> 27:04.201
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

27:08.830 --> 27:09.819
[ Cellphone beeps ]

27:09.830 --> 27:11.491
Hey, Artie, what's up?

27:11.500 --> 27:13.912
Raji's tracker brought me
to this woman's house.

27:13.920 --> 27:16.878
Picked her up and took her
to the Irvington.

27:16.880 --> 27:18.871
A no-tell hotel.

27:18.880 --> 27:20.416
Okay, I'll meet you there.

27:20.420 --> 27:22.456
[ Cellphone beeps ]

27:22.460 --> 27:23.916
Thanks.

27:37.460 --> 27:39.530
You know, the only thing missing
from this car is a vanity plate

27:39.540 --> 27:41.246
that says "Insecure Man."

27:41.250 --> 27:43.241
Yeah, I tried.
It wouldn't fit.

27:45.500 --> 27:48.378
Well, Hoffman was a bust.
What did I miss?

27:48.380 --> 27:50.075
Raji's parked
right over there.
Mm-hmm.

27:50.080 --> 27:51.616
No sign of Tapper.

27:51.620 --> 27:53.030
Great.

27:54.750 --> 27:56.115
[ Sniffs ]

27:57.880 --> 28:00.451
You smell like sex.

28:00.460 --> 28:02.030
[ Sniffs ]

28:02.040 --> 28:03.530
And salmon.

28:03.540 --> 28:05.667
[ Chuckles ] What?
[ Scoffs ]

28:05.670 --> 28:07.877
How are you the best private
detective in Portland?

28:07.880 --> 28:09.745
That's -- [ Chuckles ]
I mean...

28:09.750 --> 28:12.116
Shut up.
Yeah? Why don't you
tell me about your date?

28:12.120 --> 28:13.826
My date?

28:13.830 --> 28:17.038
You sound like my dad.

28:17.040 --> 28:18.576
Tell me about your dad.

28:18.580 --> 28:21.413
Eh -- I didn't...
Y-You sound like a dad.

28:21.420 --> 28:23.285
You don't sound
like my dad.

28:23.290 --> 28:26.077
Tell me about your dad,
anyway.

28:26.080 --> 28:27.206
I don't talk about him,
okay?

28:29.710 --> 28:31.200
If you say so.

28:34.960 --> 28:37.576
I have a daughter.

28:37.580 --> 28:40.117
She lives in Chicago.

28:40.120 --> 28:42.748
She's a teacher.

28:42.750 --> 28:45.992
We didn't talk for a while,
about 10 years...

28:46.000 --> 28:50.619
[ Inhales deeply ]
She had problems, mostly drugs.

28:50.620 --> 28:53.612
But I never gave up
on her.

28:53.620 --> 28:56.453
I wanted to.

28:56.460 --> 29:00.328
I hated her for the hell
she put me through, but...

29:00.330 --> 29:02.412
10 years later,
we're finally in a good place.

29:05.290 --> 29:08.077
You, uh --
You kind of remind me of her.

29:08.080 --> 29:09.877
[ Chuckles lightly ]
Yeah?

29:12.620 --> 29:14.747
You should call your dad.

29:14.750 --> 29:17.116
Just saying.

29:17.120 --> 29:18.997
You might regret it
at some point if you don't.

29:19.000 --> 29:21.457
[ Exhales sharply]

29:21.460 --> 29:25.112
Didn't you say people
don't change?

29:25.120 --> 29:27.577
I say a lot of crap.

29:27.580 --> 29:28.660
[ Chuckles softly ]

29:28.670 --> 29:29.739
There we go.

29:29.750 --> 29:32.162
Okay. Fingers crossed
Tapper comes out.

29:32.170 --> 29:34.240
We put the sidepiece
in our vise,

29:34.250 --> 29:36.320
get her to flip,
cash the check --

29:36.330 --> 29:37.877
[ Engine starts ]
...then off to Outback.

29:37.880 --> 29:40.030
What?
Outback Steakhouse.

29:40.040 --> 29:43.032
Amazing establishment.

29:43.040 --> 29:44.280
[Vehicle departing ]

29:44.290 --> 29:45.370
Alright.

29:45.380 --> 29:47.166
Raj and Bree
are on the move.

29:48.540 --> 29:50.417
Okay, there he is.
Alright.

29:53.580 --> 29:55.377
Bloomin' Onion,
here we come.

29:55.380 --> 29:56.870
[ Gunshots ]
[ Grunts ]

29:56.880 --> 29:57.915
[ Breathing shakily ]

30:01.170 --> 30:03.570
[ Frequency ringing ]
[ Breathing heavily ]

30:03.580 --> 30:05.707
-Medic!
-[ Screams ]

30:05.710 --> 30:07.200
Medic!

30:08.880 --> 30:11.781
[ Grunts ]
It's okay.

30:11.790 --> 30:13.667
[Tires squeal ]

30:13.670 --> 30:15.240
Whoa! Whoa!

30:15.250 --> 30:17.457
It's my former client,
Danny Dongelberg.

30:17.460 --> 30:19.496
Oh, my God! [ Chuckles ]
I can't belive it.

30:19.500 --> 30:21.491
Dongelberg.
That's his real name.

30:21.500 --> 30:23.286
I mean, this guy -- he hired me,
he didn't pay me,

30:23.290 --> 30:25.281
so I had to, uh --
[ Chuckles ] --

30:25.290 --> 30:26.780
I had to garnish his wages.

30:26.790 --> 30:29.372
Shut up! It's not funny, okay?
Just stop!

30:29.380 --> 30:31.075
Are you okay?

30:31.080 --> 30:32.377
I'm fine. I'm fine.

30:34.500 --> 30:37.879
This is, uh -- This is
private investigating, Dex.

30:37.880 --> 30:39.324
You're not doing
your job right

30:39.330 --> 30:41.207
unless a few folks
want you dead.

30:44.170 --> 30:46.377
[ Engine starts ]

30:46.380 --> 30:47.745
[ Exhales sharply]

