Bye.
Yeah.

31:38.710 --> 31:40.701
Hey, Frank.

31:40.710 --> 31:42.371
Grey McConnell?

31:42.380 --> 31:43.995
Old friends popping up
all over the place.

31:44.000 --> 31:45.820
A word, please?

31:45.830 --> 31:49.459
It's fine.
One was a handsome man

31:49.460 --> 31:51.917
Believe it or not,
you were my next house call.

31:51.920 --> 31:53.706
Oh, yeah?
Well, uh...

31:53.710 --> 31:56.247
[ Clears throat ]
That's 8K.

31:56.250 --> 31:58.411
It's all the cash I got. Please.
The rest is tied into the bar.

31:58.420 --> 31:59.614
It's just a little gesture,
for the big man.

31:59.620 --> 32:00.871
It's for Kane.

32:00.880 --> 32:02.370
I do visit him
from time to time.

32:04.330 --> 32:05.661
I want you to know
I'm not Jackie.

32:05.670 --> 32:08.912
I'm not running.
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, I heard about that.

32:08.920 --> 32:10.456
Sounds like [exhales sharply]

32:10.460 --> 32:11.996
he finally crossed
the wrong person.

32:12.000 --> 32:14.958
[ Billiard balls clack]

32:14.960 --> 32:16.575
I can pay.
Mm-hmm.

32:16.580 --> 32:18.707
I just need time,
but Kane's in jail for life,

32:18.710 --> 32:20.416
and I'm not going anywhere,
you know? My life is here.

32:20.420 --> 32:22.240
I got people here
who depend on me,

32:22.250 --> 32:23.820
people I don't want
to put in any sort of danger.

32:23.830 --> 32:26.037
$500,000.

32:26.040 --> 32:27.667
Not $250,000.
That's insane.

32:27.670 --> 32:32.619
That is what you owe
because your pal was an idiot.

32:32.620 --> 32:35.578
Just make sure that bar of yours
stays profitable, Grey.

32:42.330 --> 32:44.491
[ Inhales deeply ]

32:44.500 --> 32:46.206
We know you're Tapper's
new love interest,

32:46.210 --> 32:48.030
and I'm gonna
be brutally honest,

32:48.040 --> 32:50.611
this is not gonna end well
for you, Bree.

32:50.620 --> 32:53.919
Here you go.
[ Clears throat ]

32:53.920 --> 32:55.911
Randall is the first man
I've dated

32:55.920 --> 32:58.070
who's been up front
about what he wanted.

32:58.080 --> 33:00.071
And so was I.

33:00.080 --> 33:02.537
But now,
it's more than that.

33:02.540 --> 33:04.781
So, why would I help you
take down my boyfriend

33:04.790 --> 33:06.496
to help that psycho
he's divorcing?

33:06.500 --> 33:07.819
Look, you might not
want to work with us.

33:07.830 --> 33:09.661
You don't know us.
I get it, okay?

33:09.670 --> 33:11.570
But before you say no,
you should really

33:11.580 --> 33:13.741
talk to someone
who knows the real Randall.

33:18.460 --> 33:19.916
How long before
he took you to Rome?

33:23.330 --> 33:27.243
The morning
after our first date.

33:27.250 --> 33:29.411
I had to wait two days.

33:29.420 --> 33:32.207
He told me he loved me
on the plane ride back.

33:32.210 --> 33:36.283
I was f-frozen, shocked.

33:36.290 --> 33:38.781
But it was the way
he looked at me

33:38.790 --> 33:41.998
that finally turned me...

33:42.000 --> 33:45.322
made me think
that this could be real.

33:45.330 --> 33:47.116
He said my dreams
were his dreams.

33:49.710 --> 33:55.068
When I got pregnant,
he didn't...

33:55.080 --> 33:57.662
He wanted me
to have an abortion.

33:57.670 --> 33:59.035
I wouldn't.

33:59.040 --> 34:00.576
He insisted.

34:00.580 --> 34:02.616
I wouldn't.

34:02.620 --> 34:04.827
He choked me,
he slapped me,

34:04.830 --> 34:08.379
I hit him back.
That made him angrier.

34:08.380 --> 34:10.496
He tried to make my life
a living hell

34:10.500 --> 34:13.708
in hopes that I would
change my mind.

34:13.710 --> 34:15.530
I wouldn't.

34:17.040 --> 34:19.668
[ Rattling ]

34:19.670 --> 34:23.618
It is the only thing
I don't regret these days

34:23.620 --> 34:27.374
about...

34:27.380 --> 34:29.166
[sniffles] everything.

34:34.830 --> 34:36.377
[ Exhales sharply]

34:36.380 --> 34:38.746
I think I have something
that might help.

34:38.750 --> 34:41.207
[ Laughing ]

34:45.710 --> 34:48.167
[ Inhales sharply ]
Disgusting.

34:48.170 --> 34:50.286
He's definitely not gonna fight
Candace for custody,

34:50.290 --> 34:53.248
and he's gonna have to pay,
big time.

34:53.250 --> 34:56.037
I'll handle it from here.

34:56.040 --> 34:59.282
You did some really good work,
Dex.

34:59.290 --> 35:02.168
Honestly.
We make a good duo.

35:02.170 --> 35:03.614
[ Chuckles lightly ]
Rip City Dicks?

35:03.620 --> 35:05.326
Oh.

35:05.330 --> 35:08.993
You are
a strange...strange man.

35:09.000 --> 35:10.160
See you around?

35:11.330 --> 35:12.991
[ Engine starts ]

35:18.670 --> 35:19.819
Dongelberg.

35:21.750 --> 35:22.876
[Tires screech ]

35:22.880 --> 35:24.279
You're a friggin' maniac!

35:24.290 --> 35:26.611
You're working for a maniac!
You bitch!

35:26.620 --> 35:28.167
Hey!
Oh!

35:28.170 --> 35:29.489
Oh.
What are you doing?

35:29.500 --> 35:31.536
Calling the cops
for several attempts at murder.

35:31.540 --> 35:32.529
No.

35:32.540 --> 35:34.246
Stay down!

35:34.250 --> 35:37.117
I don't know what he told you,
but Artie Banks ruined my life.

35:37.120 --> 35:39.418
Shut up.
No, I hired him to do a job.

35:39.420 --> 35:41.706
He got proof that my business
partner was stealing from me

35:41.710 --> 35:45.328
and then sold him the very same
evidence I hired him to get.

35:45.330 --> 35:47.878
It's true.
That's his game.

35:53.750 --> 35:56.241
[ Cellphone ringing ]
I was made
for loving you, baby

35:56.250 --> 35:59.071
You were made for loving me

35:59.080 --> 36:00.490
Pick up, you son of a bitch.
[Tires squeal ]

36:00.500 --> 36:01.876
Artie: You've reached
the A to the B.

36:01.880 --> 36:04.166
Please leave a may-sage.

36:04.170 --> 36:07.617
[ Beep ]
You were made for loving me

36:09.290 --> 36:11.417
This isn't right! Gah --
[ Music stops ]

36:11.420 --> 36:13.490
You sold the tape
to Tapper?

36:13.500 --> 36:14.876
Yep.
How much?

36:14.880 --> 36:16.996
More than I would have got
from Candace.

36:17.000 --> 36:19.161
Artie,
she is gonna lose her kid.

36:19.170 --> 36:21.240
That's sad.
I really mean it.

36:21.250 --> 36:22.456
_ But I'm not _
in the morality busmess.

36:22.460 --> 36:24.610
I'm a private investigator
for hire.

36:24.620 --> 36:26.167
I go where the money goes.

36:26.170 --> 36:28.206
Ugh, God,
this is so messed up.

36:28.210 --> 36:30.667
This is so --
This is so messed up.

36:30.670 --> 36:34.663
I told you exactly what I was
gonna do -- exploit, manipulate.

36:34.670 --> 36:36.535
People don't change,
remember?

36:36.540 --> 36:39.668
You took me for some doddering,
over-the-hill chump.

36:39.670 --> 36:40.819
I played to that.

36:40.830 --> 36:42.821
I told you
what you wanted to hear.

36:42.830 --> 36:45.617
I'm not your daddy.
I'm not your mentor.

36:45.620 --> 36:50.114
I'm a guy who can read people
really well.

36:50.120 --> 36:51.280
I'm gonna report you.

36:51.290 --> 36:52.951
You illegally bugged
a private citizen,

36:52.960 --> 36:54.370
put a tracking device
on a car.

36:54.380 --> 36:57.326
I didn't do those things.
You did.

36:57.330 --> 36:59.412
I did you a favor.
You did us a favor?

36:59.420 --> 37:01.206
You are
incredibly talented,

37:01.210 --> 37:03.576
but there's one thing
standing in the way

37:03.580 --> 37:05.821
of you being an exceptional
private investigator.

37:07.620 --> 37:09.827
You care.

37:09.830 --> 37:12.287
[ Sighs ]
One day, we're gonna run into
each other down the road

37:12.290 --> 37:14.576
on a gig,
and you will thank me.

37:14.580 --> 37:16.161
Bon voyage, kid.

37:16.170 --> 37:17.455
How are you gonna look
Candace in the eye

37:17.460 --> 37:18.609
and tell her
what you did?

37:18.620 --> 37:21.282
I'm not.

37:21.290 --> 37:22.575
[ Pen clicks ]

37:25.460 --> 37:28.031
I, uh...

37:28.040 --> 37:29.871
I never met Chaka Khan.

37:29.880 --> 37:31.745
And I don't have a daughter.

37:31.750 --> 37:33.286
[ Exhales sharply]

37:42.580 --> 37:44.957
That's not gonna make you
feel any better.

37:47.330 --> 37:48.911
[ Sighs ]

37:52.750 --> 37:53.956
Feeney. It's Grey.

37:53.960 --> 37:55.416
Yeah,
I'm just checking in, man.

37:55.420 --> 37:57.661
I_...I want to see
if you left town

37:57.670 --> 37:59.786
and if our friend reached out
to you again, okay?

37:59.790 --> 38:00.870
Hit me back.

38:00.880 --> 38:03.075
Okay, so I lied
to an off-duty cop.

38:03.080 --> 38:04.115
You see my problem?

38:04.120 --> 38:05.246
I've got a dead body,

38:05.250 --> 38:07.070
you've got a history
with the victim,

38:07.080 --> 38:09.457
you were in contact with him,
and you lied about it.

38:09.460 --> 38:11.667
Am I a suspect?
You're the only suspect.

38:11.670 --> 38:13.206
Well, why don't you
just ask me if I killed Feeney?

38:13.210 --> 38:14.609
Go ahead and ask.
You don't have an alibi.

38:14.620 --> 38:15.746
I was at the bar.
Alone.

38:15.750 --> 38:17.240
That's not an alibi.

38:17.250 --> 38:18.956
Well, I was there.

38:18.960 --> 38:21.702
You're hiding something.

38:21.710 --> 38:24.417
It's not a crime.

38:24.420 --> 38:25.660
I don't want to stick you
with a murder

38:25.670 --> 38:28.958
if you didn't do it,
but I will find something on you

38:28.960 --> 38:30.609
if you don't cooperate.

38:30.620 --> 38:31.609
[ Exhales sharply]

38:31.620 --> 38:33.451
It's blood from a stone,
man.

38:33.460 --> 38:36.611
I don't know what Dex knows
about your past,

38:36.620 --> 38:39.498
but I'm pretty sure
she wouldn't be too happy

38:39.500 --> 38:41.877
to know she's playing house
with a potential murderer.

38:41.880 --> 38:44.166
Man, I was wondering
if this was all about Dex.

38:44.170 --> 38:46.707
You got it twisted if you think
that's how I go about my job.

38:46.710 --> 38:48.109
[ Knock on door ]

38:49.920 --> 38:51.035
[ Exhales sharply]

38:54.040 --> 38:55.610
[ Door closes ]

39:08.580 --> 39:10.821
You didn't murder Feeney.
[ Exhales sharply]

39:10.830 --> 39:13.492
My guys got CCTV feeds
from nearby.

39:13.500 --> 39:16.572
We got you going into the bar
late that night,

39:16.580 --> 39:17.956
getting out
early in the morning.

39:17.960 --> 39:19.370
I got to tell you something --

39:19.380 --> 39:20.779
uh, I also didn't
kill Biggie or Tupac.

39:20.790 --> 39:22.417
The list goes on.

39:22.420 --> 39:23.785
It's endless, really, of all
the people I didn't kill.

39:23.790 --> 39:25.371
I think you do know
who killed him.

39:25.380 --> 39:27.746
I think I'm gonna go.
I think that's my right.

39:27.750 --> 39:29.456
So, this was fun.

39:29.460 --> 39:31.200
I think you and Feeney
got wrapped up

39:31.210 --> 39:32.780
in something
with your prison crew.

39:32.790 --> 39:35.076
Feeney went left,
took a couple bullets,

39:35.080 --> 39:36.286
now you're left
holding the bag.

39:38.210 --> 39:40.747
I put Wallace Kane away,
you know?

39:40.750 --> 39:43.162
I know him. Well.

39:43.170 --> 39:45.741
Killed one of my C.I.'s
a few years back.

39:45.750 --> 39:48.617
One of probably 50 bodies
that he dropped.

39:48.620 --> 39:50.997
IfI was under his thumb,
I'd be afraid,

39:51.000 --> 39:52.991
whether he was
in jail or not.

39:53.000 --> 39:55.787
I'd want help.
Protection.

39:55.790 --> 39:57.496
And you'd be willing
to do me a solid, huh?

39:57.500 --> 40:00.663
If you help me find
Feeney's killer.

40:00.670 --> 40:03.616
Before he kills you.
[ Sighs ]

40:03.620 --> 40:05.872
This offer's for right here,
right now.

40:05.880 --> 40:07.529
Tomorrow?

40:07.540 --> 40:11.032
I come after you.

40:11.040 --> 40:14.373
Just do me a favor --
leave Dex out of this,

40:14.380 --> 40:17.531
whatever it is
you think you're doing.

40:17.540 --> 40:19.201
[ Knock on door ]

40:23.830 --> 40:25.320
[ Door closes ]

40:25.330 --> 40:27.491
[ Siren wailing distantly ]

40:34.710 --> 40:36.450
[ Foot tapping ]

40:36.460 --> 40:37.575
[ Sighs ]

40:41.040 --> 40:42.530
Ah!
[ Tape deck whirs ]

40:42.540 --> 40:44.496
[ Snap!'s "The Power" plays ]

40:46.250 --> 40:47.911
I've got the power

40:47.920 --> 40:49.535
Power

40:52.620 --> 40:53.917
[ Engine starts ]

40:53.920 --> 40:55.740
I've got the power

40:55.750 --> 40:57.706
Power

40:57.710 --> 40:59.826
[ Knock on door ]

40:59.830 --> 41:01.912
Hey.

41:01.920 --> 41:02.989
Um...

41:03.000 --> 41:03.910
I've got the power

41:03.920 --> 41:05.956
Today, I got beat.

41:05.960 --> 41:08.872
I lost. We lost.

41:08.880 --> 41:12.372
Artie sold me out,
and it [exhales sharply]

41:12.380 --> 41:13.995
it pisses me off,
and it pisses me off

41:14.000 --> 41:18.414
that my mistake
could cost you your child.

41:18.420 --> 41:20.786
But they're not gonna
get away with this, okay?

41:20.790 --> 41:22.030
No, they think
we're just gonna lie down

41:22.040 --> 41:24.531
and we're gonna take it.

41:24.540 --> 41:26.110
Yeah, you know,
they have the power

41:26.120 --> 41:28.327
and they have
the influence and...

41:28.330 --> 41:29.376
But you know what?

41:29.380 --> 41:31.166
They're arrogant
sons of bitches,

41:31.170 --> 41:33.161
and they don't know that women
like us have been fighting

41:33.170 --> 41:35.491
our entire lives
for everything.

41:37.790 --> 41:39.030
Randall's gonna pay,

41:39.040 --> 41:41.076
and Artie's gonna pay
for what he did.

41:41.080 --> 41:43.878
And I...

41:43.880 --> 41:44.949
I won't lose again.

41:44.960 --> 41:46.780
I've got the power
